---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import {
  LEGAL_EFFECTIVE_DATE,
  LEGAL_VERSION,
  SITE_NAME,
} from "../../lib/site";

const description = `Terms of Service for ${SITE_NAME} — draft, pending legal review.`;
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Service"
  description={description}
  canonicalPath="/legal/terms"
>
  <article class="max-w-2xl">
    <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.28em] text-[color:var(--color-accent)]">
      Legal
    </p>
    <h1
      class="font-display mt-3 text-4xl leading-[1.1] font-medium tracking-tight text-[color:var(--color-ink)] sm:text-5xl"
    >
      Terms of Service
    </h1>

    <dl class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap gap-x-8 gap-y-2 text-sm text-[color:var(--color-muted)]">
      <div>
        <dt class="uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-xs">Version</dt>
        <dd class="mt-1 text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">{LEGAL_VERSION}</dd>
      </div>
      <div>
        <dt class="uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-xs">Effective</dt>
        <dd class="mt-1 text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">
          {LEGAL_EFFECTIVE_DATE}
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div>
        <dt class="uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-xs">Status</dt>
        <dd class="mt-1 text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">
          Draft — pending legal review
        </dd>
      </div>
    </dl>

    <aside
      role="note"
      class="mt-8 rounded-lg border border-[color:var(--color-hairline)] bg-[color:var(--color-surface)] p-4 text-sm text-[color:var(--color-muted)]"
    >
      This document is a placeholder. It has not been reviewed by counsel and
      does not yet reflect the final Terms of Service that will govern use of
      Podex. Content will change materially before general availability.
    </aside>

    <div
      class="prose prose-neutral mt-10 max-w-none text-[color:var(--color-ink)] [&_h2]:font-display [&_h2]:mt-10 [&_h2]:text-2xl [&_h2]:tracking-tight [&_p]:mt-4 [&_p]:leading-relaxed [&_ul]:mt-4 [&_ul]:list-disc [&_ul]:pl-6 [&_li]:mt-1"
    >
      <h2>1. Acceptance of these terms</h2>
      <p>
        By accessing Podex you agree to these Terms of Service. If you do
        not agree, please do not use the site. Continued use after we publish a
        new version constitutes acceptance of that version.
      </p>

      <h2>2. What Podex is</h2>
      <p>
        Podex is a podcast discovery service. It lets you browse a
        curated catalog of podcasts and, where available, related episodes,
        media, and mentions. Podex does not host third-party audio; it links to
        and describes shows produced by others.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Acceptable use</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Do not attempt to disrupt, overload, or reverse-engineer the service.</li>
        <li>
          Do not scrape the site at a rate or in a manner that degrades it for
          other users; use documented APIs and reasonable rate limits.
        </li>
        <li>
          Do not use Podex to violate applicable law or the rights of
          podcast owners, guests, or other users.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4. Third-party content</h2>
      <p>
        Podcast titles, descriptions, artwork, and audio remain the property of
        their respective owners. Podex surfaces this content for
        discovery only, and any views expressed in podcasts are those of the
        creators, not of Podex.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Accounts</h2>
      <p>
        Account features are not yet available on this site. Once accounts
        launch, additional terms specific to accounts, subscriptions, and
        billing will be added here and offered for acceptance.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Disclaimers</h2>
      <p>
        The service is provided on an "as is" and "as available" basis, without
        warranties of any kind, express or implied, to the fullest extent
        permitted by law.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Limitation of liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the extent permitted by law, Podex and its contributors will
        not be liable for indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or
        punitive damages arising out of or related to your use of the service.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Changes to these terms</h2>
      <p>
        We may update these terms as the product evolves. When we do, we will
        bump the version and effective date shown above. Prior versions will
        remain retrievable so that acceptance records stay meaningful.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about these terms can be sent to the project maintainers via
        the project repository until a dedicated contact address is published.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
